.TH CRYPT.PL 1 "27 Feb 2006" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_NAME@ utils"
        
.SH NAME
crypt.pl, encrypt \- encrypt files received from \fBrdup -c\fR

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B crypt.sh
.IR KEYFILE
[
.IR OPTIONS
]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBcrypt.pl\fR, by default,  encrypts the data it receives from \fBrdup\fR with the
key contained in \fIKEYFILE\fR.
.PP
For example,
.PP
        rdup -c list ~/Documents | crypt.pl KEY | mirror.pl -c -b /tmp/storage
.PP
Note the \fI-c\fR option for \fBmirror.pl\fR.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c
This option is ignored, \fBcrypt.pl\fR always works on the files'
content. This "feature" was added because all rdup-util scripts have
such an option.
.TP
.B \-d
Decrypt the files.
.TP
.B \-V
Show the version.

.SH SEE ALSO
gzip.pl(1), mirror.pl(8) and mcrypt(1).
